Create a local git repository and move the entire codebase to it

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"

Create a new branch for a new feature you want to add to the application

git checkout -b new-feature

3. **Merge back the created branch with the master branch.**

git checkout master
git merge new-feature

4. **Create a remote repository.**

created as per instruction. 
https://github.com/stsgit2022/DevOps-August

5. **PUSH the local repository to the company's remote repository.**

git remote add origin https://github.com/stsgit2022/DevOps-August/edit/main/Assignment-1
git push origin master

extra.

* `git status` - shows the status of the current repository
* `git log` - shows the commit history of the repository
* `git diff` - shows the differences between two versions of the repository
